{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fcfbf243-cf8a-4247-9d6f-b6ae253e4e75","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them. But here's how you can analyze your `.dmp` file:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze`\n\n```bash\n# Install the tool if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Start analysis\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\n### Key commands inside the analyzer:\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` / `printexception` | Show the last exception (start here) |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `clrstack` | Show managed call stack for current thread |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a specific thread |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `gcroot <addr>` | Find what's keeping an object alive |\n| `exit` | Quit |\n\n### Typical workflow:\n1. Run `pe` to see if there's an unhandled exception\n2. Run `threads` to find the faulting thread\n3. `setthread <id>` → `clrstack` to inspect its stack\n4. Use `dso` to examine objects on the stack\n\n### Alternatives:\n- **Visual Studio** (Windows): File → Open → File → select `.dmp` → \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n- **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS): `lldb --core your-file.dmp` then `loadsymbols` + `clrstack`\n\nWould you like me to walk you through any of these steps in more detail?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"895d258c-d8a1-4e6d-9d28-aadc21abb06d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET crash dump file (.dmp) and wants to analyze it to find the root cause. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo I shouldn't use that skill. Let me provide guidance on how to analyze a .dmp file instead.\n\nI should help them use `dotnet-dump analyze` or similar tools. Let me check what tools are available in the environment first, but I can also just give them guidance.\n\n\nI'll focus on giving them practical steps for analyzing the dump file themselves rather than trying to use tools I'm not equipped for.","outputTokens":576,"requestId":"1B8A:3BD16D:FD8AD0:11FC66B:6A02882C"},"id":"47a00a85-7b02-4ae1-a2c0-da47ff9d99f2","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:54:02.899Z","parentId":"51e33c07-774a-47ba-b53f-0e0c3afe89eb"}
